      <h3 id="champions">Champions</h3>
      <p>Must be lightweight, with focus on providing infrastructure, starting use cases, adjudicating conflicts, and applying funding to projects (sparingly).</p>
      <p>CodeX Accelerator serves this purpose for Use Cases around cancer (mCODE standard), cardiovascular disease, and genomics, so far. Other governance schemes are possible but would require more effort to startup and engage across specialties.</p>
      <p>Large, medical professional societies and Government organizations have been the most frequent CodeX Champions for most Use Cases, but other stakeholders have also been effective Champions.</p>
      <p>Ability to understand needs, reach all constituencies, and mobilize resources are key.</p>

<h4 class="h5">Engage specialty and Use Case Champions early in the process</h4>

Champions are organizations and individuals who:
<ul>
<li>are willing to lead</li>
<li>understand the problems</li>
<li>believe the SHR approach is a key part of future solutions</li>
<li>command the attention of their larger community and influence others to engage</li>
<li>motivate vendor implementation of SHR and its use in health processes</li>
<li>muster the resources needed to succeed</li>
<li>drive one more key stages of the initiative: Community Engagement, Use Case Prioritization, Standards Development, Implementation & Pilots, Adoption & Value</li>
</ul>
      <h3 id="governance">Governance</h3>
